  "prompt": "Why won\u2019t the maps on my Apple Watch series 2 work without a phone connection?",
  "response": "On Apple Watch Series 2, maps and navigation typically require a connection to an iPhone because the watch itself does not have built-in GPS or cellular capabilities for standalone navigation. The watch relies on the iPhone for:\n\n1. GPS data\n2. Cellular data connection\n3. Downloading map data\n\nWhile Series 2 has its own GPS, it still needs the iPhone for full map functionality and data retrieval. Later models like Series 3 and newer with cellular options can function more independently for navigation.\n\nIf you want standalone maps, you might consider upgrading to a newer Apple Watch model with cellular capabilities.",
